{
  "stem": "4361.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We worked at the Weberei until about-- again, I cannot give you the exact month.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was fall.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was very cruel work, because we were given-- well, let me say what we were supposed to do in the Weberei.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were supposed to make long, rope-type things out of old clothes, tear it up and then sort of put it together, knot it together, and then make rolls out of it.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Until this day, I don't know what the purpose of it was, except I think they were used for some sort of fuses.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'm sure they were used for some war material.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And a certain quota was assigned every day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she who didn't make the quota-- and most of us didn't-- were badly kicked, beaten, slapped by the [GERMAN], by the SS woman in charge.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[SIGHS] The only advantage, if it can be called that, the only advantage of working in the Weberei was that you were in an enclosed environment.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And various SS couldn't grab you for various things, or you weren't hit, you weren't beaten by anyone else except the SS supervisor.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, one nice day, when we went out early in the morning to stand [? seil ?] appell, an SS came, conversed, conferred with the Lager [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were told to go back into our blocks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Later on we found out, within a day or so, that the Weberei, which consisted of one big building-- as I remember made of wood, and it had several compartments where we worked-- this place was blown up.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It didn't exist.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was the end of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I am jumping ahead.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "About 10 years ago, I found out what happened at a wedding in Vail, Colorado.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was winter, and we were in Vail.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
